original_title: Frank Sinatra: A Man and His Music
overview: The first-ever Sinatra television special in color, this 1965 performance showcases the Chairman in peak form to mark the occasion of Frank Sinatra's 50th birthday.. The Nelson Riddle arrangements sparkle, opening with a classic rendition of I've Got You Under My Skin and continuing on with other favorites such as I Get A Kick Out Of You, Come Fly With Me and The Lady Is A Tramp.
tagline: Frank Sinatra: A Man and His Music
title: Frank Sinatra: A Man and His Music Part I
